description: This issue of 'Sad Sack' was used in the cult film The Lost Boys. About sixteen minutes into the movie you see a girl in the back of a car laughing out loud at the comic while her boyfriend is trying to kiss her.

Wolverine may be back in S.H.I.E.L.D. custody, but at what cost? As the X-Men mourn their fallen team-mate in a funeral befitting a hero, Hydra celebrates the coronation of a new leader. And the reign of terror continues, as The Hand picks off the meta-humans, one by one… Will Wolverine be deprogrammed in time to stop the carnage? Plus, the secret origin of the Gorgon!
name: Agent Of S.H.I.E.L.D., Part 1

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: What’s scarier than a high-profile super hero turned deathcult assassin? TWO super heroes turned deathcult assassins! Hydra might have lost Wolverine, but two more take his place, and one is a former X-Man who will shock former teammates and readers alike! As the new Supreme Hydra launches an unprecedented attack on S.H.I.E.L.D., there’s precious little time for second guesses, leaving Nick Fury to send Wolverine into the heat of battle hoping the deprogramming will stick.
name: Agent Of S.H.I.E.L.D., Part 2

description: This issue answers point blank the question: Did Superman know the actions of the other JLA team members during Identity Crisis? This special issue examines the fallout from the earth-shattering IDENTITY CRISIS! Superman, shaken by Lois' shooting and the events in IDENTITY CRISIS, looks to consult with Batman and Wonder Woman, and neither have the time or interest in helping him. Are the pillars of the DCU starting to crack?
name: The Road to Ruin, Part One

description: Superman was about to found out who Ruin was, but couldn't. Jimmy ges hurt and Lois gives Clark a tremendous surprise news.
name: The Road to Ruin, Part Two

description: Mr. Mxyzptlk shows Clark and Lois a possible future were they have a daughter that grows to be a super powered hero.
name: The Road to Ruin: Narrative Interruptus Tertiarius

description:
Part two of the three-part “Lightning Strikes” arc, bringing together Superman and Captain Marvel by the creative team of Winick, Churchill and Rapmund! Superman confronts the evil force plaguing Metropolis. What will Superman do when some of his closest allies turn against him?

Eclipso manages to get Superman angry by possessing Lois Lane, and now he has taken control of Supemran's body. When everything seems lost, Captain Marvel appears.

Next: Superman Vs. Captain Marvel.
name: Lightning Strikes Twice Part 2

description:
Ocean Master has taken over Aquaman's life, and the real Aquaman is now the Ocean Master! Chaos erupts as Aquaman realizes all is not as it seems, especially when a secret from his past comes back to haunt him in ways he could never have imagined!

Ocean master and Aquaman have switched lives!Chaos erupts as Aquaman realizes that a secret from his past comes back to haunt him in ways he could never have imagined.Can Aquaman break the dreaded that grips the citizens of the deep?!?
name: Retroverse Two: Brother vs. Brother!

description:
The majority of the earth's surface is water, and Aquaman rules it all! But is it too much for just one man to protect and serve? Some Sub Diegans think so, and they've decided they want their very own guardian. But are they ready for the tougher, meaner Malrey?

Lorena in her new alias as Aquagirl begins showing off her new costume to Aquaman who voices his disappointment at her desire to even wear one before leaving to supervise the visits by boat between the surface citizens and the citizens of Sub Diego.Meanwhile Hector continues his journey exploring the sea,only to meet Vulko and the Atlantean navy who are searching for Sub Diego.While elsewhere a local reporter continues to try to get Aquaman to give her an interview, giving him her card for if he changes his mind. The returning citizens are then attacked by a swarm of sharks with Aquagirl preparing to protect the citizens until a mutated monster attacks the school of sharks,with Aquaman arriving to learn he is a police officer by the name of Alonzo Malrey who is going to help out in Sub Diego.Aquaman then returns to Geist who is responsible for mutating the officer. Geiest then shows Aquaman a recording of a corporation which through the use of Sub Diego volunteers has copied the gene for water breathing which originally came from Aquman himself.
name: To Serve & Protect

description:
A rush of applications for GeneTech's water-breather gene therapy leads to chaos! Aquaman goes to the JLA to gain leverage against GeneTech, but finds the group in the middle of its own problems, as the Themyscira crisis heats up! And Malrey is badly hurt in battle with Conger!

Aquaman then sets out to deal with Progene Tech, while giving officer Malrey a warning to see the city council first before patrolling or they will be enemies.While back in the city Vulko and the navy arrive to meet with Aquaman to tell him of his restoration to the throne of Atlantis,however he adamantly refuses the offer.Vulko then declares he is taking ten citizens back to Atlantis for a goodwill tour, as Aquaman goes to the JLA watchtower where he meets with Superman. The two begin to exchange words before Superman attacks and the two have a short battle before it's revealed to be a shapeshifted Martian Manhunter.Aquaman then calls Esther Maris, who arrives at Progene Tech to speak to the CEO.
name: Undertow

description: On the day of the launch of a mysterious new book, 'The Mars Conspiracy', the book's author, editor and printers are killed, the warehouse is burned to the ground and the launch bookshop is destroyed. Oracle sends Batgirl to the library to track down the copy that will have been added to their stock as a legal deposit. Here, Batgirl encounters a librarian who helps her stop the strange robotic creature which attempts to burn the library down in order to destroy the book. The library is saved, but the book is destroyed. Later, Batgirl encounters Spoiler, who tells her that Batman has fired her from her position as Robin, but she won't give up on crime-fighting.
name: Cooking the Books

description: Batgirl saves a four-year-old boy from a mob hit, alerting Oracle to the fact that innocents have now become targets in the gang war which is sweeping the city. They then get word that a number of children are being held hostage at Louis E. Grieve Memorial High, Tim Drake's school. On the way there, Batgirl encounters Spoiler, who is out on the streets doing her best to help. She tells the younger hero to stay off the streets and makes her way to the school, hitching a ride from a television news helicopter. Once there, she and all the bystanders hear a single gunshot.
name: War Games: Act I, Part 6 - Total War

description: Batman saves a woman from a sniper who is holding the street on behalf of what was Lew Moxon's gang. She then makes her way to Leslie Thompkins' clinic and asks her if she's seen Spoiler. Leslie has not, and asks Batgirl to leave her to her work. Meanwhile, Tommy Elliot offers to tell Black Mask where to find the Batcave. Within minutes of Batgirl and Leslie's conversation, the clinic is attacked by Lynx and the Ghost Dragons, who plan to have the clinic as their own personal medical facility. Leslie refuses, and Batgirl comes to the clinic's defence. She fights off the Ghost Dragons, but in the process, one of them accidentally decapitates Lynx. Leslie is furious that Batman's violent world has spilled over into her clinic, and demands that Batgirl leaves once more.
name: War Games: Act 2, Part 6: Collateral Damage

description: Oracle asks Batgirl to give Onyx a hand. Onyx has found herself cornered by members of Killer Croc's gang, but with the arrival of Batgirl, the two women are able to turn the tables on the thugs. Meanwhile, Black Mask commandeers journalist Arturo Rodriguez and his film crew for the scoop of a lifetime, as he leads the criminal classes of Gotham City on an assault on the Batcave. Only, as Oracle soon realises, Black Mask's information (from Tommy Elliot) is slightly wrong, and the building he thinks of as the Batcave is actually Oracle's clocktower.
name: War Games: Act 3, Part 6: Ground Zero

description: "Fresh Blood" part 2, continued from ROBIN #132. Cassandra teams up with Robin to pick up the pieces from the events of "War Games," but can these crime-fighting teens stop the lethal blades of Nightwing's archnemesis, Shrike? Continued in ROBIN #133.
name: Fresh Blood Part Two: Following Footsteps

description: Batgirl and Robin are forced to fight to the death, but of course, Robin has a plan and Batgirl is able to read his body language to work out what it is. Robin beats her and then shoots her at close range, seemingly killing her. However, Batgirl is able to stop her heartbeat, so when the Penguin gets close enough, she springs into action and the two of them escape from the mansion, battling past a number of the villains in Penguin's employ as they do so. Back at Robin's apartment, they recognise that they are very different from one another and disagree on many things, but they also make a good team. Batgirl is looking forward to the opportunity to do things her way in a new city, and to being able to work with Robin when the need arises.
name: Fresh Blood Part Four: Settling Up

description: Batgirl is beginning to settle in Blüdhaven and is receiving combat training from Onyx. She makes some important fist steps, including acquiring an underworld snitch named Marquis and a headquarters courtesy of Batman and Alfred. She also discovers that something big is going down - the Penguin has a delivery coming. However, she doesn't know that the Brotherhood of Evil are in town.
name: The Hood, Part One: Deep Digs

description: When Batgirl goes to the local café for some tea, she discovers that McSweeny Realty, who have sold many local properties, are trying topressure the owner, Brenda Miller, into selling as well. Of more immediate importance, though, is the arms shipment that the Penguin is apparently receiving. Batgirl discovers that someone has been posing as a customs official, and encounters this person - Gemini - aboard the dead official's houseboat. She soon finds herself up against Gemini, Mallah and the Brain, odds which are too high for her, and she is left for dead, soon seeing an apparition of her late friend Stephanie, a.k.a. Spoiler.
name: The Hood, Part Two: Into the Light

description: Batgirl is drowning, but is saved by the spirit of Spoiler, who encourages her to fight for her life, and also helps her remember some things from her past. Later, Batgirl begins a tentative friendship with Brenda Miller, and also tips the police off about the Penguin's arms deal with the Brotherhood of Evil. Unfortunately, someone in the police department tips off the Penguin, who escapes, but Batgirl is able to defeat the Brotherhood.
name: The Hood, Part Three: Dead Weight

description: Batman is pleased with the work that Batgirl is doing in Blüdhaven, including using a Wayne Foundation grant to help those home and business owners under pressure to sell to McSweeny Realty. Meanwhile, the villainous Society are not at all pleased with Batgirl's presence in the city, due to her disrupting the arms deal with the Brotherhood of Evil. They send Deathstroke in to finish her off, and he soon attracts her attention by putting innocents in danger. She engages him, but soon realises that he's toying with her - he actually intends her to fight his daughter, the Ravager.
name: Could've Been, Part One: Nowadays

description: Overview The ultimate gang war has engulfed Gotham City, and it’s about to strike close to home for one member of the Batman family. With Scarface shooting it out against gun-toting thugs, can Batman and company keep innocents from falling in the crossfire?
name: Last Stand at Alamo High

description: Upon learning that Black Mask has seized Oracle's clock tower, Batman routes everybody to the scene. The police have the site surrounded, but they're ordered to arrest anyone in a mask or costume, and to use lethal force if they don't comply. Batman races to confront Black Mask, leaving his associates to take care of any of Gotham's more notorious criminals that might try to escape the building. The Scarecrow is transformed by the serum in his blood into the monstrous creature that recently terrorized Gotham. Robin, Onyx, Catwoman and Batgirl spring into action, promising to surrender to the authorities after they've stopped Crane. Inside, Batman's fight with Black Mask threatens to claim both their lives. To end he conflict, Oracle activates the clock tower's self destruct mechanisms, leaving her survival in Batman's hands. But no sooner has he gotten her out of the ruins when the call comes in from Leslie... Stephanie doesn't have long left.
name: War Games, Act 3, Part 8: No Going Back

description:
War Games, Epilogue:

Bruce told Dick about Stephanie. He took down some illegal arms dealers after he left her at the Thompkins Clinic. At that moment, he forgot two things: Oracle was gone and Tim didn't know. He went to tell Robin his girlfriend was dead. Days later, Tim's father died. Bruce had spoken with Stephanie's mother at her grave side and called her a hero. She called Batman a criminal.

They went over the rest of the situation - Robin and Batgirl were in Bludhaven while Dick recovered from the bullet he took to the leg. Black Mask appeared to be in complete control of Gotham's underworld.
name: War Games, Epilogue: Decompression

description: Batman learns that someone unknown has managed a hostile takeover of Kord industries, which is WayneTech's research and development unit, responsible for a number of the items he uses in his war on crime. Meanwhile, as Black Mask continues to increase his grip on Gotham's underworld, a new player makes himself known. The Red Hood, who insists that his drug dealer stay away from kids. In response, Black Mask recruits yet another of Gotham's supercriminals - Mister Freeze.
name: Under the Hood, Part 1: New Business

description:
Overview

Part 2 of the 4-part "Under the Hood," featuring the new Batman team of writer Judd Winick, artists Doug Mahnke and Tom Nguyen and cover artist Matt Wagner. The Black Mask and the new Red Hood carve up the Gotham underworld -- and Batman continues to reel from a startling revelation as "Under the Hood" continues! Is Gotham headed toward another Gang War?

Spoilers



Nightwing joins Batman in Gotham while he recovers from his leg injury. The Black Mask has a suit made for Mr. Freeze and finds out about a new guy in town: the Red Hood. Batman and Nightwing intercept a shipment of super villain weaponry, only to find the ship its on rigged with explosives. They chase the saboteur, the Red Hood, but lose him when they run into Amazo.
name: Under the Hood, Part 2: First Strike

description: Mr. Freeze and Black Mask argue about their working relationship when Black Mask finds out that there's been no confirmation of his latest shipment. Meanwhile, Batman and Nightwing are fighting Amazo, part of that shipment. After destroying him, they search for his remain to confirm he's no longer a threat. Back at Black Mask's headquarters, he recieves a call from the Red Hood about a box of kryptonite.
name: Under the Hood, Part 3: Overnight Deliveries

description: At the scene of Amazo's attack, Batman picks up kryptonite radiation. Elsewhere, Red Hood and Black Mask negotiate for the kryptonite, settling at fourteen million dollars. Black Mask sends Mr. Freeze to kill Red Hood and get the kryptonite back. On the streets, Batman and Robin track the radiation trail. At a factory somewhere in Gotham, Red Hood figured that Black Mask would trick him and tries to kill Mr. Freeze. Batman and Nightwing show up and both villains flee. Red Hood tracks down the Joker to an abandoned amusement park and beats him with a crowbat before removing his mask and revealing himself to be Jason Todd.
name: Under the Hood, Part 4: Bidding War

description: Red Hood has changed his game, destroying the Black Mask's shipments rather than stealing them. Meanwhile, Batman consults Zantanna and Jason Blood about ways to bring people back to life. In Gotham, Onyx breaks up a group of drug dealers and finds out that the Red Hood is running Gotham's drug trade. In Star City, Batman asks Green Arrow about coming back to life. Meanwhile, Onyx spies on a group of drug dealers when she's confronted by none other than the Red Hood.
name: Family Reunion, Part 1: The Word on the Street

description:
A thief is stealing priceless diamonds in Gotham City, and the cops are hot on the trail of Catwoman for the crime. The Batman knows she's innocent, but will he be able to stop the police?

Priceless Diamonds are being stolen around Gotham City. The officers at Gotham PD are hot on the trail of Catwoman, but the weird thing is she's innocent! Batman must clear her name and find who the real criminals are before it is too late for both of them! Join this exciting adventure of "Batman Strikes!"
name: The cat's prize

description:
Mr. Freeze wants a piece of Gotham City all to himself, and what Freeze wants, Freeze gets! Only Batman's cunning and technology will be able to save Gotham from being put on ice.

Mr. Freeze claims a piece of Gotham! Batman must use his amazing gadgets and skills to stop this icy foe. Can Batman save his city before it is to late? Join Batman against Mr. Freeze in this comic with chilly greetings.
name: Icestorm

description:
Gotham City's never been hotter, which can only mean one thing: Firefly's back. Batman must stop this pyromaniac before Gotham is reduced to ash!

Firefly has big plans for Gotham. He intends to reduce Gotham City into a smoking pile of ashes. Batman must stop this pyromaniac, before he gets burnt and the rest of Gotham City! Join Batman in this great comic.
name: Firefall

description: Overview As gang war rages, Batman and Batgirl must save the innocent and stem the violence. Batman launches an effort to turn the tides of war, but he reckoned without Tarantula!!
name: War Games: Act 1 Part 4, Rules of Engagment

description: Overview With Gotham City plunged into a blackout, Tarantula attempts to take down the Penguin…but she’s gonna have to get through Deadshot first! Meanwhile, Hush makes a decision that will have a devastating impact on the gang war!
name: War Games: Act 2 Part 4, The Light at the End of the Tunnel

description: Overview With the city in chaos, Tarantula becomes the prime target of the G.C.P.D.! Desperate for a victory, they’re hell-bent on bringing her down. Batman must choose between stemming the violence and saving his newest ally.
name: War Games: Act 3 Part 5: Flight Risk

description: Following an explosion, Batman and Mister Freeze are trapped inside a bubble of ice which is itself inside a burning building and beginning to melt. Despite their differences, they must work together to escape from certain death.
name: Fire & Ice

description: Alfred in action! Alfred in an accident! Alfred kidnapped by Hush! As Batman searches frantically for his friend, Alfred makes plans of escaping on his own.  While escaping he comes across something -- someone -- that could change everything Batman and Alfred thought they knew about Hush!
name: The Games People Play

description: Some orphan children, two years after Gotham City's devastating earthquake, become suicidal.  Mayor Hull visits Zhang, a chemical weapons cartel industrialist who is conducting experiments on Gotham City teens without families.  Poison Ivy recognizes the names and faces of the suicide victims. She realizes that these children were surviving with her and her plants in Robinson Park.  She reads the medical examiner's report for one death and believes that she somehow has poisoned them.  She searches for some of the other Robinson Park orphans who are still alive.
name: Human Nature, Book One

description:
Poison Ivy arrives at the scene of another teen suicide to inform Batman that she is not the cause of the suicide.  She asks Batman to contact Bruce Wayne for help in finding whoever is causing these suicides.

Ivy breaches Fluorotech's security and searches through Jason Woodrue's research, hoping she can find a way to prevent any further deaths.
name: Human Nature, Book Two

description:
Gotham City Police suspect that Poison Ivy is the cause of the deaths of orphan teens, a cop, and a man in an elevator. They are unable to apprehend Ivy because Hush intervenes. Ivy kisses Hush at his request and realizes that he has developed some anti-toxin that can negate her pheromones and toxins. She asks Hush for his help, but he refuses to help her change back to her non-toxic human form.

Mayor Hull again meets with Zhang and expresses his displeasure about the mounting number of deaths. Zhang offers more bribe money to keep the mayor covering up who is actually behind these deaths.

Ivy conducts research to determine what caused her transformation into a toxic being.  Full of remorse, Ivy becomes obsessed about restoring herself to her non-toxic human form so that she can no longer harm anyone else. She again seeks out Bruce Wayne, a man with money who can finance her transformation.
name: Human Nature, Book Three

description: A massive power vacuum at the top of Gotham's top gangs has lead to Batman's nightmare scenario... all of the city's organized crime are striking out at once. The police aren't the only ones completely unequipped to handle this kind of situation, as Batman finds that he, Catwoman and Batgirl are woefully inadequate to quiet the menace. Reaching out to Orpheus, who he has placed in charge of the Hill mob, he begins working to consolidate the gangs under Orpheus' control.
name: War Games: Behind Enemy Lines

volume.name: Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight

description: Batman's efforts to contain the violent gang warfare that has erupted throughout Gotham aren't enough. Even though Tim Drake has once more taken up the Robin costume to help, Batman is unable to fight an entire city full of crime... and now he's strained his relationship with the relatively new Police Commissioner Akins. Deciding that he can do more good in another guise, he once more dons the identity of 'Matches' Malone, trying to gather information from the underworld, as well as make contact with whoever has orchestrated this chaos. Little does he know, that this devestation was accidentally started by Stephanie Brown, after he dismissed her as Robin. Attempting to prove herself to him, she tried to implement a plan she'd previously found in the computers of the batcave. But in not knowing all of Batman's secrets, she failed. Catwoman is the only one who knows, and she's sworn not to tell Bruce. But telling Leslie... that's different.
name: War Games: Philosophical Differences

volume.name: Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight

description: Overview As Batman drowns in a sea of enemies, the rest of Gotham’s heroes race to save him! All the chaos and violence so far was merely a prelude to this. To make matters worse, the G.C.P.D. is about to break ranks!
name: War Games: The Road to Hell

volume.name: Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight

description: Part 1 of the 5-part "Riddle Me That", the ultimate Riddler story! Someone is using riddles in the kidnapping of an influential Gotham City doctor. But the crime is more brutal than anything the Dark Knight has experienced with Edward Nigma. Who's the madman behind it all?
name: Riddle Me That Part One

volume.name: Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight

description: There's an all-new Riddler wreaking havoc on the streets of Gotham--and he's three steps ahead of the Bat. Can Batman save a nosy graduate student from an horrific death and stop a bombing on a local commuter train?
name: Riddle Me That Part Two

volume.name: Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight

description: Part 3 of the 5-part "Riddle Me That!" The transformation of Edward Nigma from second-rate has-been to villainous mastermind is revealed! And all the while, Batman careens from a fiery wreck atop a towering bridge!
name: Riddle Me That Part Three

volume.name: Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight

description: The Riddler's plan continues as he managed to fool Batman.
name: Riddle Me That Part Four

volume.name: Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight

description: Batman thought to have beaten the Riddler at his game but founds himself outsmarted by him.
name: Riddle Me That Conclusion

volume.name: Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight

description: Mr. Freeze began robbing some seemingly random items. Batman get into investigation without finding the link for these items. When he finally confronts him, Freeze reveals his newest and strange plan.
name: Cold Snap Part 1

volume.name: Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight

description: It's the final showdown between the Birds and Thorn in the thrilling conclusion of the explosive "Hero Hunters," a finale no reader should miss! Don't say we didn't warn you ? this issue will be the most talked-about of the year!
name: Hero Hunters, Part Five: The Cold Light of Day

description: A new era begins with the debut of art team Joe Bennett (HAWKMAN, Captain America & The Falcon) & Jack Jadson and cover artist Adriana Melo (ROSE & THORN)! Huntress has gone AWOL, and you'll be shocked at where she turns up! Who's taking her place next to Canary on a dangerous mission to Singapore? None other than Wildcat, as "The Battle Within" begins!
name: The Battle Within, Part 1- Undefended Border

description: Haunted by his personal failures, Captain America comes to suspect that he has been under psychological attack from the rogue Navy Intelligence unit that created the so-called "Anti-Cap" Super Soldier
name: Brothers and Keepers (Part 1): Death By Design

description: MODOK's origin is revealed as the Mental Organism Designed Only for Killing continues stalking former A.I.M. agents across Europe. Cap attempts to broker a cease-fire with Navy Intelligence. But, although the fate of the Anti-Cap appears to be resolved, the government refuses to drop criminal charges against The Falcon, which in turn pushes The Falcon to even more extreme measures. But, has he gone too far this time?
name: Brothers and Keepers: Part 2: Hunters/Brothers & Keepers: Part 2 of 5

description: "Brothers & Keepers (Adelphoite Phylaxes)," part 3 of 5. The Falcon's increasingly erratic behavior has created sharp conflict between Captain America and himself. While Cap works with S.H.I.E.L.D. agent Ali Morales and S.H.I.E.L.D. commander Nick Fury to track down the deadly A.I.M. leader M.O.D.O.K. and ferret out MODOK's connection to rogue Naval Intelligence Admiral "Jimmy" Westbrook, Falcon proceeds on his own track, unleashing the newly-restored and re-powered Anti-Cap to help destroy the Rivas drug cartel, and, hopefully, bag Admiral Jimmy and MODOK at the same time.
name: Brothers and Keepers: Part 3: The Killers Club/Brothers and Keepers: Part 3 of 5

description: "Brothers & Keepers (Adelphoite Phylaxes)." Cap tracks MODOK to his secret lair but discovers the unexpected: MODOK doesn¹t know him! Time¹s running out! What¹s happened to MODOK and, ethically, should Cap do anything about it? Meanwhile, the Falcon has gone AWOL in mid-mission, leaving Cap and the Anti-Cap to settle the score once and for all. Part 4 of 5.
name: Brothers & Keepers: Part 4 of 5/Brothers and Keepers: Part 4: I, M.O.D.O.K.

description:
Brothers & Keepers (Adelphoite Phylaxes)"

Cap pursues a distraught and suicidal MODOK to Singapore, where Cap must come between MODOK and an enraged INCREDIBLE HULK. For, if Hulk kills MODOK, MODOK will unleash the deadly MODOK Virus, which threatens the entire planet! Meanwhile, S.H.I.E.L.D. Agent Ali Morales confronts Falcon on his recent odd behavior and forges an unlikely alliance. Part 5 (of 5).
name: Brothers & Keepers (Part 5)

description:
"American Psycho" Part 1 (of 2)

Because of the Falcon’s increasingly erratic behavior, Captain America is forced to sever his long-time partnership with The Falcon while the Anti-Cap goes on a murderous rampage.
name: American Psycho (Part 1)

description: Series conclusion! Distraught over his choices and their deadly consequences, the Falcon has set out to correct his mistakes— starting with recapturing Captain America’s Navy counterpart, the so-called "Anti-Cap." Realizing his partner has taken on the deadly Anti-Cap alone, Captain America sets off after the Falcon— which leads to the final battle between the two Captains as the Falcon’s fate hangs in the balance.
name: American Psycho (Part 2)
